FBIS3-39465 "drweu033__a94032" FBIS-WEU-94-033-A Document Type:Daily Report 17 February 1994 ANNEX France Poll Shows Majority Support Air Strikes in Bosnia BR1502101194 Paris LE POINT in French 12 Feb 94 p 29 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1502101194 Paris LE POINT Language: French Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "IPSOS-LE POINT Opinion Poll"] [Text] A national sample of 800 people representing the French population 18 and older were polled by telephone on 8 and 9 February 1994 using the representative quotas method. Following are the results: Should French UN troops stay in Bosnia or should they be pulled out? They should stay: 58 percent They should be pulled out: 28 percent Don't know: 14 percent Should NATO bomb Serbian artillery positions around Sarajevo? Yes: 54 percent No: 29 percent Don't know: 17 percent Should French troops take part in the air strikes if NATO decides to bomb Serbian artillery positions around Sarajevo? Yes: 70 percent No: 21 percent Don't know: 9 percent Should the French authorities accept risking French military losses in the fighting taking place in the former Yugoslavia? Yes: 55 percent No: 35 percent Don't know: 10 percent
